mxCell.value: <font style="font-size: 12px;">One work flow is associated to each task </font>
Task's WF gives more systematic overview of the task wich is better than the task description (in Jira)
Users can updata their status in task's WF when they have finished one step (each task must have one active state in its WF)
If a task is taking longer than expected (or it is blocked) the effecte of this on the other linked tasks will the evaluated and reflected in the table
If a WF is updated (e.g., new steps added) the effect of this updated on the other tasks will be evaluated
If part of the WF can be handled by a Generative AI, the user will be adviced
Benefits of using our project managment strategy: Task Work Flow
1. Increases the visibility of the subtasks and the logical workflow to accomplish them
2. It enhances collaboration between users when they can model theri communication in a WF and follow up systematically
3. It organize resources or intermediate results in a logical fashion based on their underlying WF
4. It allows project mangers to identify reoccuring patterns in a WF (or even accross WFs) that are good candidates for automation using Gen AI powered systems
5. It allows PM to grow their business
1. Find a compling use case -  several tasks with their workflows - show the effectiveness of our approach
2. Link each component in WF (state, message) to the appropriate resource
Most important services we can offer
• WF of each tasks provides a systematic way of following up with the current state of each task
• PM can have a better understanding of the way each task is going to be handled by each person
• Explaining challenges and alternative ways to the PM or other stackholders will be easier
3. Automating substeps, e.g., when someone is working on some task what should happen automatically when a particular message is recived by the other teamate
